Event types represent custom Mailchimp events you want to create.

Once an event type is listed here, Drupal can create it in Mailchimp, usually through a webform handler, or custom code.

Events are not imported from Mailchimp.

For use only with text filters that use the Mailchimp Campaign filter
You can insert an entity of a given type and pick the view mode that will be rendered within this campaign section.
Subscription is pending. Confirm by visiting your email.
Choose a connected site from your Mailchimp account.
Configure paths to embed Mailchimp's JavaScript code on.

Add a campaign to use entities as campaign content.

Importing campaigns from Mailchimp is not possible.

Deleting an event type will prevent drupal from triggering the same event again, but already logged events will still exist in the Mailchimp Activity Feed.

Be sure to also delete any webform handlers and code that calls on this event entity.
A comma-separated list of fields to exclude. Reference parameters of sub-objects with dot notation. The options available match the options in "Fields".
A comma-separated list of fields to return. Reference parameters of sub-objects with dot notation. If left empty, events.name, events.properties, and events.occurred_at will be returned.

Any entity with an empty or invalid email address field value will simply be ignored by the Mailchimp subscription system. This is why the Email field is the only required merge field which can sync to non-required fields.

This displays a list of all Mailchimp Subscription Fields
        configured on your system, with a row for each unique Instance of that field.
        To edit each field's settings, go to the Entity Bundle's configuration
        screen and use the Field UI.
        When entities with Mailchimp Subscription Fields are updated,
        the Merge Variables configured through Field UI are automatically updated if necessary.
        However, if you have existing subscribers on Mailchimp and matching Entities
        on Drupal when you configure your Merge Variables, the existing values
        are not synced automatically, as this could be a slow process.
        You can manually force updates of all existing Merge Values to existing
        Mailchimp subscribers for each field configuration using the 'Batch Update'
        option on this table. The Mailchimp Subscription Field is provided by the
        Mailchimp Audiences (mailchimp_lists) module.

This is useful for "additive" form behavior, so a user adding a new interest will not have other interests removed from their Mailchimp subscription just because they failed to check the box again.
